  "prompt": "What are the natural predators of deer?",
  "response": "Deer have several natural predators, depending on their species and geographic location:\n\n1. Large predators:\n- Wolves\n- Mountain lions (cougars)\n- Coyotes\n- Bears (grizzly and black bears)\n\n2. Smaller predators:\n- Bobcats\n- Lynx\n- Foxes (typically target fawns)\n\n3. Aerial predators:\n- Eagles\n- Mountain lions\n- Wolverines\n\n4. Predators of fawns specifically:\n- Coyotes\n- Foxes\n- Eagles\n- Bobcats\n- Wolves\n\nThe specific predators vary by region and deer species. In North America, wolf and mountain lion predation is most common, while in other regions, different predator populations may be more prevalent.",
